      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HONEY RYDER (4) was prominent early from the tricky draw and did a fair job to be beaten a neck into second (29.67) at this track in a Grade 5 over 515m. Ran one of the fastest times on the program last start despite finishing in the minors. Overdue and is among the main hopes. WHISKY BELLA (1) missed the frame latest (30.60) when fourth over 525m at The Meadows in a Grade 5 H. Already a winner from this draw. Looks one of the chances. I'M EASY (6) continues to race well but is struggling to break through, placing at his last four runs. Last start finished 3rd on April 13 over 515m at this track behind Unacceptable Nik beaten 4.5 lengths (29.95) in a Grade 5. Goes well out of this box with a win and three minor placings. Well-placed to take this out. BREAKN' A SWEAT (2) is likely to have admirers.",
